  "version_pin_rationale": "fontconfig 2.13.1-4.2ubuntu5 is the jammy release build. fontconfig (the .deb) ships the fc-* CLI tools; libfontconfig1 (separate .deb, same version) ships the .so. Both are required: Hyprland's render path calls into libfontconfig for glyph lookups; first-boot needs fc-cache to populate /var/cache/fontconfig. fontconfig-config (the system-wide /etc/fonts/fonts.conf) is a transitive dep; we rely on the jammy host shipping it (same precedent as DE0-D's support-libs). dejavu-fonts is a hard dep: fontconfig with zero fonts emits 'no fonts found' and Hyprland renders empty surfaces."
